   Research Resources
   Blue Triangle Cornell University/Martin P. Catherwood Labor Library
   Cornell's award-winning web site.
   Blue Triangle Department of Labor Historical Information
   History of the Department of Labor. From the Creation of the Department
   of Labor to Biographies and Portraits of Former Secretaries of Labor.
   Blue Triangle The Economic Policy Network
   This site is a top-notch electronic clearinghouse for public policy
   information. It includes full text publications (e.g., The American
   Prospect) and the Economic Policy Institute's publications and
   catalogs. Excellent starting point for searches about labor and
   society.
   Blue Triangle Holt Labor Library
   Particularly interesting video collection, which is available for loan.
   Blue Triangle The Institute of Industrial Relations at UC Berkeley
   This site has numerous pages which provide information about faculty
   research and programs, and it includes two online faculty working
   series, several guides to labor on the Internet, and research guides
   that offer guidance for labor research.

   [bluetri.gif] The Labor Center Reporter
   Covering labor and employment since 1979, the LCR has been an important
   source of data, technical advice and commentary for labor union staff,
   members and libraries.
   Blue Triangle Labor History Web Page
   Annotated guide to reference sources on labor in the United States,
   prepared by Andrew Lee, Tamiment Institute Library, New York
   University; excludes industrial relations.
   Blue Triangle Labor Research Association
   The Labor Research Association provides a full array of research
   services for labor researchers, and their web site site is a very
   useful starting place for general information.
   Blue Triangle Multinational Monitor
   A labor magazine with an international scope.
   Blue Triangle New Work News
   An online summary of the press that covers international labor news;
   updated everyday.
   Blue Triangle Princeton University Industrial Relations Library
   Research
   This is not a comprehensive biography but a guide designed to lead you
   to the basic sources of information about industrial relations and a
   tool to help you begin your research.
   Blue Triangle Princeton University Social Science Center Reference
   Collections
   The Princeton University's Library and Collections online.
   Blue Triangle Rutgers Management and Labor Relation Library
   Blue Triangle Ryerson University Library
   Blue Triangle University of California at Berkeley Center for Labor
   Research & Education
   Blue Triangle University of Hawaii Center for Labor Education and
   Research
   This site includes interesting guides to Hawaii's labor laws, labor
   history, a directory of video programs about labor in Hawaii, and the
   definitive guide to Hawaii labor web sites.
   Blue Triangle University of Illinois at Urbana
   (Champaign Institute of Labor and Industrial Relations)
   Includes both research information and a look at the A.M. and Ph.D.
   programs.
